TopicTitle: KSP Interstellar Extended Continued Development Thread

Articles.Content: I usually just use plasma engines and stop in midair rather than generating heat on the way down..... if you have the atmosphere mining things you can get all the reaction mass you need to fly down too...  Kinda cheap but I usually splode when I try and do an atmo-brake.

Version 1.8.15 for Kerbal Space Program 1.1.2

Released on 2016-05-03

  • Increased Energy Transfer Radiator by a factor of 10
  • Added WasteHeat heatsink to Warp Drives
  • Added Conformal Graphite Radiator
  • Upgraded IFS to 1.29

the reason it has 3 warp rings is that this ship was originally designed with a mod that used the USI warp drive system, and i liked the aesthetic.

Well fortunately, in KSPI-E, the warp drives stack, which means you can warp up to 2 x 24 x 3 x 10 = 1420 mT with is bad boy. Since I don't see much other vessel mass, it means your must have a very high Warp Power to Vessel Mass ratio. As a consequence, you need less power (and fuel) to enter warp, which means a single 2.5 Antimatter reactor with Charged Particle generator and Thermal Electric Generator should be more than enough. Hack I bet even a single Fusion Reactor should be more than enough. Alternatively you could add more power to this monster to set a speed record, which will minimize the amount of antimatter fuel needed to reach a far destination. That because the faster you travel, the more  energy efficient you will be. Of cource traveling at high speed will also be more chalanging but that's part of the fun.  Still I wonder how far you can push this, perhaps even nuclear powered Warp drive would be possible.
